Sorry spatz my misunderstanding again, I shouldn't taken the word murderer as relating to me, even though it was me you were addressing in the posts above.<br><br>
There is a difference between a murderer and those that are engaged in war. I know I killed many of the enemy, but I never murdered any of them. There is a difference, except in the mind of the war protestors that used those phrases to justify their anti-war stand. <br>
I did my duty as a US servicemen and if that &quot;Gook&quot; or &quot;Commie&quot; would have killed me, he would have been doing his duty, and he tried. <br>
They shot at me, and I found it amusing that they would select to shoot at the locking pin that held my machine gun together, or to shoot the machine gun out of my hands or to shoot at the 2&quot; wide piece of rock right by my eye, or to have thrown a grenade that would only throw me back and not kill me, or to have shot all those hundreds of rounds that kicked up dust all around me, off and on for several months, they were only playing around with my mind. Guess they weren't trying to kill me. But, I wonder if they would have killed me, if their country or fellow countrymen would have called them murderers?<br>
No, instead their country honored their warriors, our country disgraced ours, why? Because of people like you, that, for what so ever reason believed we went to Vietnam to murder civilians and other south Vietnamese who were only engaged in an inner turmoil and in their own civil misunderstanding. <br>
But then you say, we should have gone for broke, &quot; faught to win,…or not faught at all.' <br>
What does that mean? Why interfere at all if it was a civil war, as you have so often said? <br>
Sounds like fish flip flopping in the lake to me, probably why I chose to see what type of bait you were using. <br>

